  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is expand explicit-formula finite zero-pair window testing with larger zero counts and additional smoothing policies before attempting any stronger bridge
  + [not_purpose] is proof, disproof, independent zero certification, critical-line authority, or universal smoothing-window ranking

  = must: preserve sharp and Fejer behavior from the earlier zero-window bridge
  = must: add Lanczos sigma and Hann smoothing policies as explicit named finite window modes
  = must: expose window definitions in the output payload
  = must: keep exact pi(x), theta(x), and psi(x) comparison rows visible
  = must: compare expanded window modes across at least x values 100, 200, and 500 and zero-pair counts 5, 10, 20, 40, and 80
  = must: preserve proof_status as finite_zero_window_probe_not_zero_certification
  = must: treat mpmath zetazero as numerical library lookup, not proof authority
  - never: infer RH proof, disproof, or zero certification from finite window residuals
  - never: treat a lower residual in one row as universal window superiority
  - never: fuse explicit-formula residual rails with Euler-product/log-derivative rails without a later source-defined shared comparison unit

& [ExpandedWindowDefinitions] is the canonical finite window set
  + [sharp] is weight(k, N) = 1
  + [fejer] is weight(k, N) = 1 - k/(N + 1)
  + [lanczos] is weight(k, N) = sin(pi*k/(N + 1))/(pi*k/(N + 1))
  + [hann] is weight(k, N) = 0.5*(1 + cos(pi*k/(N + 1)))
  + [indexing] is k ranges from 1 to N

& [ExplicitWindowExpansionTooling] is the implementation scope
  + [runtime_function] is rh_math.explicit_formula.zero_window_probe
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\zero_window_probe.py
  + [trace_output] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\analysis\zero_behavior\2026-06-26_explicit_window_expansion_trace.json
